{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[533]] &ndash; [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] general [[Belisarius]] defeats the [[Vandals]], commanded by King [[Gelimer]], at the [[Battle of Tricamarum]].
*[[1161]] &ndash; Military officers conspire against [[Emperor Hailingwang of Jin|Emperor Hailingwang]] of the [[Jin Dynasty (1115–1234)|Jin Dynasty]] and assassinate the emperor in a military camp near the [[Yangtze River]] front.
*[[1167]] &ndash; [[Kingdom of Sicily|Sicilian]] [[Chancellor]] [[Stephen du Perche]] moves the royal court to [[Messina]] to prevent a rebellion.
*[[1256]] &ndash; [[Hulagu Khan]] captures and destroys the [[Assassins|Hashshashin]] stronghold at [[Alamut]] in present-day [[Iran]] as part of the [[Mongols]] offensive on Islamic southwest [[Asia]].
*[[1467]] &ndash; [[Stephen III of Moldavia]] defeats [[Matthias Corvinus]] of [[Hungary]], with the latter being injured thrice, at the [[Battle of Baia]].
*[[1778]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] and [[France|French]] fleets clash in the [[Battle of St. Lucia]].
*[[1791]] &ndash; The [[United States Bill of Rights]] becomes law when ratified by the [[Virginia General Assembly]].
*[[1864]] &ndash; In the [[Battle of Nashville]], [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] forces under [[George Henry Thomas|George Thomas]] almost completely destroy the [[Army of Tennessee]] under [[John Bell Hood|John Hood]].
*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Hunkpapa]] [[Lakota people|Lakota]] leader [[Sitting Bull]] killed on [[Standing Rock Indian Reservation]], leading to the [[Wounded Knee Massacre]]. 
*[[1905]] &ndash; The [[Pushkin House]] is established in [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]] to preserve the cultural heritage of [[Alexander Pushkin]]
*[[1906]] &ndash; The [[London Underground]]'s [[Great Northern, Piccadilly and Brompton Railway]] opens.
*[[1913]] &ndash; [[Nicaragua]] becomes a signatory to the [[Buenos Aires Convention]].
*[[1914]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The [[Serbian Army]] recaptures [[Belgrade]] from the invading [[Austro-Hungarian Army]].
*  1914   &ndash; A gas explosion at [[Mitsubishi]] Hojyo coal mine, [[Kyushu]], [[Japan]], kills 687.
*[[1917]] &ndash; World War I: An armistice is reached between the new [[Bolshevik]] government and the [[Central Powers]].
*[[1933]] &ndash; The [[Twenty-first Amendment to the United States Constitution]] officially becomes effective, repealing the [[Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Eighteenth Amendment]] that [[Prohibition in the United States|prohibited]] the sale, manufacture, and transportation of [[Alcoholic beverage|alcohol]].
*[[1939]] &ndash; ''[[Gone with the Wind (film)|Gone with the Wind]]'' receives its premiere at [[Loew's Grand Theatre]] in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia]], [[United States]].
*[[1941]] &ndash; [[The Holocaust|Holocaust]]: [[Nazi Germany|German]] troops murder over 15,000 [[Jews]] at [[Drobytsky Yar]], a ravine southeast of the city of [[Kharkiv]], [[Ukraine]], [[Soviet Union]].
*[[1942]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Mount Austen, the Galloping Horse, and the Sea Horse]] begins during the [[Guadalcanal Campaign]].
*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Occupation of Japan]]: General [[Douglas MacArthur]] orders that [[Shinto]] be abolished as the state religion of [[Japan]].
*[[1946]] &ndash; US-backed Iranian troops evict the leadership of the breakaway [[Republic of Mahabad]], putting an end to the [[Iran crisis of 1946]].
* 1946    &ndash; The first [[French India Representative Assembly election, 1946|election to the Representative Assembly of French India]] was held.
*[[1954]] &ndash; The [[Charter for the Kingdom of the Netherlands]] is signed.
*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Richard Paul Pavlick]] is arrested for attempting to blow up and assassinate the [[President of the United States|U.S. President]]-Elect, [[John F. Kennedy]] only four days earlier.
*  1960   &ndash; King [[Mahendra of Nepal]] suspends the country's constitution, dissolves parliament, dismisses the cabinet, and imposes direct rule.
*[[1961]] &ndash; In [[Jerusalem]], [[Israel]] [[Adolf Eichmann]] is sentenced to death after being found guilty of 15 criminal charges, including charges of crimes against humanity, crimes against the Jewish people and membership of an outlawed organization.
*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Project Gemini]]: [[Gemini 6A]], crewed by [[Wally Schirra]] and [[Thomas P. Stafford|Thomas Stafford]], is launched from [[Cape Canaveral|Cape Kennedy]], [[Florida]]. Four orbits later, it achieves the first [[space rendezvous]], with ''[[Gemini 7]]''.
*[[1967]] &ndash; The [[Silver Bridge]] collapses, killing 46 people.
*[[1970]] &ndash; Soviet spacecraft ''[[Venera 7]]'' successfully land on [[Venus]]. It is the first successful soft [[List of landings on extraterrestrial bodies|landing on another planet]]
*  1970   &ndash; [[South Korea]]n ferry ''Namyong Ho'' capsizes off [[Korea Strait]] killing 308.
*[[1973]] &ndash; [[John Paul Getty III]], grandson of American billionaire [[J. Paul Getty]], is found alive near [[Naples, Italy]], after being kidnapped by an Italian gang on July 10, 1973.
*  1973   &ndash; The [[American Psychiatric Association]] votes 13–0 to remove [[homosexuality]] from its official list of [[Mental disorder|psychiatric disorder]]s, the [[Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|DSM-II]].
*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Samoa]] becomes a member of the [[United Nations]].
*  1976   &ndash; The oil tanker {{MV|Argo Merchant}} runs aground near [[Nantucket]], [[Massachusetts]], causing one of the worst marine oil spills in history.
*[[1978]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Jimmy Carter]] announces that the [[United States]] will recognize the People's Republic of [[China]] and cut off all relations with [[Taiwan]]
*[[1993]] &ndash; [[History of Northern Ireland]]: The [[Downing Street Declaration]] is issued by British [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] [[John Major]] and Irish [[Taoiseach]] [[Albert Reynolds]].
*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Palau]] becomes a member of the United Nations.
*[[1997]] &ndash; A chartered [[Tupolev Tu-154]] from [[Tajikistan]] crashes in the desert near [[Sharjah (emirate)|Sharjah]], [[United Arab Emirates]] airport killing 85.
*  1997   &ndash; The [[Southeast Asian Nuclear-Weapon-Free Zone Treaty|Treaty of Bangkok]] is signed allowing the transformation of [[Southeast Asia]] into a [[Nuclear-weapon-free zone]].
*[[2000]] &ndash; The 3rd reactor at the [[Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant]] is shut down.
*[[2001]] &ndash; The [[Leaning Tower of Pisa]] reopens after 11 years and $27,000,000 to fortify it, without fixing its famous lean.
*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Latvia]] amends its [[Constitution of Latvia|constitution]] to eliminate possibility of same-sex couples being entitled to [[Same-sex marriage|marry]].
*  2005   &ndash; Introduction of the [[Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor|F-22 Raptor]] into [[United States Air Force|USAF]] active service.
*[[2006]] &ndash; First flight of the [[Lockheed Martin F-35 Lightning II|F-35 Lightning II]].
*  2006   &ndash; [[Clay Regazzoni]] dies in a road traffic accident
*[[2009]] &ndash; [[Boeing]]'s new [[Boeing 787 Dreamliner]] makes its maiden flight from [[Seattle|Seattle, Washington]].
*[[2010]] &ndash; A boat carrying 90 [[Refugee#Asylum seekers|asylum seeker]]s [[2010 Christmas Island boat disaster|crashes into rocks]] off the coast of [[Christmas Island]], Australia, killing at least 30 passengers.

